{"questionId":"9069250","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Magnesium is a reactive metal often found in alloys.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Iodomethane is used to prepare CH<sub>3</sub>Mg<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math>. It can also be converted into methanol:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">CH<sub>3</sub><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math>&nbsp;+ HO<sup>–</sup> → CH<sub>3</sub>OH + <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math><sup>–</sup></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Identify the type of reaction.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«nucleophilic» substitution<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>SN2 ✔</p>\n<p><em><br>Accept “hydrolysis”.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept SN1</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069250","referenceCode":"22M.2.sl.TZ1.3f(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Identify the type of reaction.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"f(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}